turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes.  The real cause of that rile was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, come on, you knew there was nothing in that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort.  You took presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Presents?  A trivial little broach.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Mmm Hmm.  I remember it well.  Bristling with diamonds in the worst possible taste.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not at all.  It was very pretty.  I still have it and I wear it often.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No I didn't.  You made up the whole thing in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must admit he was in love with you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just a little perhaps but nothing serious.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You let him kiss you. You said so.  What of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well what of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well it didn't harm him, in fact, it pleasured him a lot and it didn't hurt me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: And what about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, if you hadn't been so suspicious and nosey you would've never known anything.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, that's a nice point of view I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Look, I'm bored with this conversation.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yeah, so am I.  Bored stiff.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You want some brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No thanks.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll have a little I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't know why you want it.  You've already had two glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No particular reason.  Anyhow they were very small ones.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see what you have to go on and on with this kind of thing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh my...just because I just...okay...

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: ...having three small minute liquor glasses in the evening is hardly going on and on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's become a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You needn't be so grand just because you don't happen to want any yourself at the moment.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be so stupid.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Really Amanda.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nothing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: [BREATHING]

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Going out somewhere dear?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, just making myself beautiful for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That reply has broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: That's the woman's job to lure the man.  Watch me a moment won't you?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Actually that's perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No it isn't.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, be quiet.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I think you should have some more brandy...

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I think that

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: ...cause really

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: it doesn't seem to be working on you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: perhaps maybe you should've had more brandy, it might've made you a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well it really hasn't worked wonders with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Hmm, snap, snap, snap like a little adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Adders don't snap, they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes they do.  They have a bag of venom behind their fangs and they snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't care.  I don't care.  Do you understand?  I don't care if they roll around and bark like hoops.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Did you see much of Peter Burden after our divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I did.  Quite a lot.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I suppose you let him kiss you a great deal more then?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Mind your business.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Mmm, you must've had a riotous time.  No restraint at all, very enjoyable.  You never had much anyhow.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're quite insufferable.  I expect it's because you're drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm not in the least bit drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You've always had a weak head.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Okay, like I mentioned before I had three very small, minute liquor glasses of brandy.  That's not even enough to get a child of two drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: On the contrary, a child of two can get violently drunk off just one glass of brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, what an interesting topic.  What about a child of four and a child of six?  A child of nine?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: We might be able to bring up a splendid little debate about this intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not very funny dear.  In fact, maybe you better have some more brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, thanks.  I think I will.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You better turn that off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Because people upstairs will get annoyed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There aren't any people upstairs.  This is a photographer's studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well there are people downstairs I suppose.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They are away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, this is no time to be in here for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again, please.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No I'll do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Very well.  If you insist on being a boorish and idiotic.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Come on, turn it off.  It's driving me mad.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You are far too temperamental.  Try to control yourself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it--Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Go away.  Go away.  I hate you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very amusing indeed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I hate you.  Listen I'm sick and tired of listening to you, you sadistic bully.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You know what?  You're a vile, little, evil-minded, little, wicked beast and I never want to see you again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: This is the end.  Understand?  This is the end, here and now, forever and always.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not going nowhere. No you're not.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, yes I am. Yes I am and you can't stop me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Just shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: shut up. shut up.  I would-I would never marry you again if you came crawling back to me on your hands and knees because you're an evil-minded little vampire and I hope to God I never see you again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Listen, you're a cruel fiend and I hate, loathe you.  Thank God finally, finally thank God I've realized just how horrible you are--and marry you?  Marry you?  Never. I will never marry you.  I will die die in torment-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Beast. Brute. Cad. Swine. Beast. Beast. Brute. Devil. Sorry.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh.
